## Why This Is Asked

This question tests practical multi-tenant data isolation, cross-project access, and production-grade analytics pipelines with Dataflow, Vertex AI, and GCS, plus governance controls.

## Key Concepts

- Multi-tenant isolation with per-tenant buckets and datasets
- Signed URL validation, secure data ingestion
- Dataflow pipelines with per-tenant routing
- Vertex AI training orchestration and guardrails
- IAM least privilege, VPC Service Controls, data residency
- Audit logging and correlation IDs

## Code Example

```javascript
// Example Cloud Function snippet for validating signed uploads
exports.validateSignedUrl = (req, res) => {
  const { signature, tenantId } = req.query;
  if (!signature || !tenantId) return res.status(400).send('Invalid');
  // Real systems verify HMAC with tenant secret from Secret Manager
  res.status(200).send('ok');
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test per-tenant data isolation and data residency?
- How would you implement a rollback if a tenant's data ingestion fails?

## Why This Is Asked
Assesses real-time streaming design, multi-tenant isolation, data residency, and production-grade reliability in GCP.

## Key Concepts
- Pub/Sub exact-once hints, Dataflow streaming, stateful processing
- Per-tenant IAM, separate buckets/service accounts, residency
- Hybrid scoring: rules engine + Vertex AI
- Dead-letter routing, canary deployments, observability

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudocode: streaming transform sketch
class ScoreDoFn {
  process(event) {
    const score = ruleScore(event) + mlScore(event);
    emit({ tenant: event.tenantId, id: event.id, score, ts: event.ts });
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate idempotence and exactly-once guarantees at scale?
- How would you test tenant isolation across regions and handle schema evolution?
